1
00:00:00,290 --> 00:01:45,030
♪

2
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:55,160
♪

3
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,120
Misao had learned
the real story

4
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,040
of Shogo's childhood.

5
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,060
She explained to us
the terrible tragedy

6
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:03,080
that had taken place
in Shimabara all those

7
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,200
years ago.

8
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:07,190
Young Shogo had witnessed
his mother's murder and all

9
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:09,120
his Christian friends crucified

10
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,190
by men who hated Christians.

11
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:13,240
Even though he had
escaped with his life,

12
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:16,010
he vowed then and there
to take his revenge on

13
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:19,000
the Japanese authorities
for allowing this massacre.

14
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,250
Even as we learned
the secret story

15
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:23,020
of Shogo's past,
we discovered Santo

16
00:02:23,020 --> 00:02:24,250
having what appears to be
a clandestine meeting

17
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:26,190
with an army of men.

18
00:02:26,190 --> 00:02:28,080
Who are they and
what are they up to?

19
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:31,080
There's no telling what
will happen next to all of us.

20
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:37,050
♪

21
00:02:37,050 --> 00:02:39,040
Lady Magdalia,
it looks as though

22
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,220
you've run out of time.

23
00:02:40,220 --> 00:02:42,140
You are scum!

24
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:43,240
Huh?

25
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,020
(gasping)

26
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:52,190
♪

27
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:59,270
♪

28
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:01,270
What are your wishes, Sir Kaiou?

29
00:03:01,270 --> 00:03:04,200
♪

30
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:08,240
Kill them, I want Lady Magdalia
and her pesky friends to die.

31
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,190
Right.

32
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:20,000
♪

33
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,230
(grunting)

34
00:03:21,230 --> 00:03:25,130
♪

35
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:27,280
(gasping)

36
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,210
Oh no!

37
00:03:28,210 --> 00:03:35,230
♪

38
00:03:35,230 --> 00:03:38,150
Who...

39
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:41,020
are you?

40
00:03:41,020 --> 00:03:42,230
I am Ramon.

41
00:03:42,230 --> 00:03:45,210
Kaiou ordered me to eliminate
anyone who gets in the way

42
00:03:45,210 --> 00:03:47,090
of our plans.

43
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:49,070
Too bad for you.

44
00:03:49,070 --> 00:03:51,000
It sounds like Kaiou's
running the show

45
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,260
instead of Shogo.

46
00:03:52,260 --> 00:03:54,240
But why does he want
to get an army involved

47
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:57,200
and whose army
is it anyway?

48
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:59,190
You'll never know that!

49
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:02,100
♪

50
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:05,160
Those kunai spears
should do the trick!

51
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,140
What?

52
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:12,200
Huh?

53
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:23,030
♪

54
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:24,080
No, don't!

55
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:36,120
♪

56
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,100
He's gonna fall!

57
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:45,010
♪

58
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:48,010
I-I can't.

59
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,110
Nice move!

60
00:04:53,150 --> 00:04:54,250
Hey.

61
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,160
(rumbling)

62
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,280
Huh?

63
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:58,140
Huh?

64
00:04:58,140 --> 00:05:00,000
It's an earthquake!

65
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,140
I don't think so.

66
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,250
Well then, what is it?

67
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:05,110
It feels more like
an underground cave-in.

68
00:05:05,110 --> 00:05:07,010
It feels pretty close
to where Sano and I

69
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:09,080
split up, we'd better hurry.

70
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:22,060
(grunting)

71
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:25,080
Sayo, are you okay?

72
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:26,270
I think so.

73
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:28,090
And Shozo?

74
00:05:28,090 --> 00:05:31,190
Oh, my gosh, he's...
he's pinned under that rock!

75
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:35,020
He shielded you, Sayo,
but now he's half-buried.

76
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:42,010
♪

77
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:44,010
Shozo, are you hurt?

78
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,250
It's all right, I'm here.

79
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:49,200
Lady Magdalia, are
you all right, milady?

80
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:50,210
Please answer.

81
00:05:50,210 --> 00:05:52,250
Put my mind to rest.

82
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:55,170
Yes, thanks to
your help, I'm fine.

83
00:05:55,170 --> 00:05:57,200
♪

84
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,250
Shozo, even as a child,
you were always willing

85
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:04,120
to help others, even at
great personal sacrifice.

86
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:06,050
That's what you taught:

87
00:06:06,050 --> 00:06:09,100
the life of a Christian
is based upon giving service

88
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:11,270
to God's will and God's people,

89
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:16,030
no matter what the price
is to us individually.

90
00:06:16,030 --> 00:06:19,000
You've learned well,
but I've never seen someone

91
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,040
so willing to put
God's word into practice.

92
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,090
(sobbing)

93
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:26,290
♪

94
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:28,090
Don't cry, Lady Magdalia.

95
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:30,270
Don't waste your tears on me.

96
00:06:30,270 --> 00:06:34,150
And besides, I'm not
going to die anytime soon.

97
00:06:34,150 --> 00:06:37,230
I have too much left to do,
so don't worry about me.

98
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:40,000
We will help you, Shozo.

99
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,150
There's gotta be
a way to rescue him.

100
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:43,150
Huh?

101
00:06:43,150 --> 00:06:51,060
♪

102
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:53,130
I'm not a Christian,
Lady Magdalia,

103
00:06:53,130 --> 00:06:57,010
but Shozo saved my life
and I wanna save him.

104
00:06:57,010 --> 00:07:06,110
♪

105
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:08,070
I can't believe
this is happening.

106
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:11,280
Lady Magdalia's
gonna save me again.

107
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:14,120
(grunting)

108
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:26,130
♪

109
00:07:26,130 --> 00:07:27,090
It's moving!

110
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:29,160
Don't stop, keep pushing!

111
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:33,140
That's it!

112
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:34,270
It's almost off!

113
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:36,170
(grunting)

114
00:07:36,170 --> 00:07:47,050
♪

115
00:07:47,050 --> 00:07:48,140
(coughing)

116
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:51,080
♪

117
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:54,010
Lady Magdalia!

118
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:55,060
(coughing)

119
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:56,220
It must be the dust
that's making you cough

120
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:58,190
so badly.

121
00:07:58,190 --> 00:08:01,040
Look there, Shozo's free!

122
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,190
Dust isn't what's
making her cough.

123
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:05,050
Lady Magdalia is ill

124
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:06,250
and yet, she risked
making herself worse

125
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:09,110
just to help me.

126
00:08:09,110 --> 00:08:12,200
(coughing)

127
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:15,090
It was God that set you free.

128
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:17,170
You must do us a favor, Shozo.

129
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:20,060
You must tell my
brother about Kaiou

130
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:22,280
before he kills many people.

131
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:24,270
As you wish, milady,
but I can't just leave

132
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:26,160
you here all alone.

133
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:28,170
Go tell Shogo
about Kaiou's plans.

134
00:08:28,170 --> 00:08:29,200
I'll be fine.

135
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:35,280
♪

136
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:37,030
It's one of Kaiou's men!

137
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:48,210
♪

138
00:08:48,210 --> 00:08:51,050
You get out of here!

139
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:55,070
Lady Magdalia, what are
you still doing alive?

140
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:56,190
Looks like I'll
have to bury you

141
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:57,240
and your gutless friends.

142
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,080
Not while I'm here!

143
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,180
Wait, Shozo, you can't beat him

144
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:02,090
after what you
just went through!

145
00:09:02,090 --> 00:09:04,110
But you could go
and tell Shogo.

146
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:07,100
He has to know all
about Kaiou's evil plans.

147
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:10,160
I give you my word,
I will protect Lady Magdalia

148
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:12,120
to the death.

149
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,020
Take these with you.

150
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:15,050
They are highly explosive
when you drop them.

151
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:16,150
A friend got them
for me in China.

152
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:17,210
You might need them.

153
00:09:17,210 --> 00:09:20,180
Take them, Shozo,
and go quickly!

154
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:21,220
I trust you.

155
00:09:21,220 --> 00:09:23,220
I will go and tell Shogo

156
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:26,060
and I will succeed
with God's help.

157
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:33,270
Hey, bald boy.

158
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:35,260
Whaddaya say we have
a real fight to the death?

159
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:36,250
(growling)

160
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:45,150
♪

161
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:48,060
You stay here while I
take care of this guy.

162
00:09:48,060 --> 00:09:51,200
Great, I finally get a chance
to show off to Lady Magdalia.

163
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:55,010
♪

164
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,000
You're gonna tell me something

165
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,080
or I'll see you suffer!

166
00:09:57,080 --> 00:10:00,060
♪

167
00:10:00,060 --> 00:10:03,100
I'd say you're the one
that's gonna suffer!

168
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:05,030
I don't think so, cueball!

169
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:24,120
♪

170
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,090
Now die!

171
00:10:25,090 --> 00:10:38,020
♪

172
00:10:38,020 --> 00:10:40,230
Now I wanna know,
just where is that medallion?

173
00:10:40,230 --> 00:10:43,160
♪

174
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,140
Tell me!

175
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:50,090
♪

176
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:52,210
Mr. Santo has got it.

177
00:10:52,210 --> 00:10:54,030
Santo's got it!

178
00:10:54,030 --> 00:10:55,260
Ha!

179
00:10:55,260 --> 00:10:58,120
(grunting)

180
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:04,030
(gasps)

181
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,190
Lady Magdalia!

182
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,200
It can't be!

183
00:11:28,290 --> 00:11:31,200
You've finally come to.

184
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,000
(groaning)

185
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,170
♪

186
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:38,000
I guess what Shozo
said earlier was right.

187
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,170
You really are very
sick, aren't you?

188
00:11:40,170 --> 00:11:42,080
That's right.

189
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:44,060
I know soon I'll
be leaving this Earth.

190
00:11:44,060 --> 00:11:45,120
(gasps)

191
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:48,180
Unless God grants me a miracle,

192
00:11:48,180 --> 00:11:51,010
I'll soon be with
Him in His kingdom.

193
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,110
(coughs)

194
00:11:53,110 --> 00:11:54,240
Don't joke about death!

195
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:57,240
You probably just have
a very bad cold or something.

196
00:11:57,240 --> 00:12:00,220
Besides, you know I
don't believe in God.

197
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,070
You think this God of yours
has the ability to control

198
00:12:03,070 --> 00:12:04,260
what happens to us?

199
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:07,200
Only a human can save
another human's life.

200
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,020
This whole concept you have,
that some divine entity

201
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:12,270
is helping you survive
on Earth is strictly hogwash.

202
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:14,180
I'll tell you what I believe in:

203
00:12:14,180 --> 00:12:15,210
friendship.

204
00:12:15,210 --> 00:12:17,260
I have real friends
that help me survive.

205
00:12:17,260 --> 00:12:19,160
Kenshin, Kori, Yoshi.

206
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:22,200
When things get really tough,
they are always there for me.

207
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,180
They can't make miracles happen,

208
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:26,050
but I trust them.

209
00:12:26,050 --> 00:12:27,190
I know that they'd
do whatever they could

210
00:12:27,190 --> 00:12:29,180
to help me no matter what.

211
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:31,250
I'm doing my best to save you.

212
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,130
I'm just asking you
to believe in me, please?

213
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:45,130
♪

214
00:12:45,130 --> 00:12:47,090
(growling)

215
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:48,230
(gasping)

216
00:12:52,060 --> 00:13:07,190
♪

217
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:08,270
Hey, Yoshi!

218
00:13:08,270 --> 00:13:11,270
It's your friend,
just like you said!

219
00:13:11,270 --> 00:13:15,090
Sano, I'd say you
owe me big-time!

220
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:17,030
Hey, Sano!

221
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,190
I'm sure glad to hear
you're still in one piece,

222
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:20,230
my friend.

223
00:13:20,230 --> 00:13:21,240
Kenshin, what's the matter?

224
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,130
Can't you see anything?

225
00:13:23,130 --> 00:13:25,190
I've lost my sight temporarily.

226
00:13:25,190 --> 00:13:27,190
But he still fights
like good old Kenshin.

227
00:13:27,190 --> 00:13:29,040
Yeah, he's got
a little vision problem,

228
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:31,210
but it hasn't cramped
his style in the least.

229
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:33,240
Oh, my, take a look
at Lady Magdalia!

230
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:40,180
♪

231
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:42,170
Kaiou is going to betray Shogo.

232
00:13:42,170 --> 00:13:45,190
Kaiou plans on ruling Japan
by murdering Shogo and stealing

233
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:47,200
all of his followers
with this Book of Prophecy

234
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,220
he's created.

235
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:51,010
By sending the army
to kill Shogo Amakusa,

236
00:13:51,010 --> 00:13:53,110
Kaiou can tell his followers
that he died like a martyr

237
00:13:53,110 --> 00:13:56,050
and take over Shogo's position
as leader of the movement.

238
00:13:56,050 --> 00:13:58,100
Kaiou must have reported
to Nagasaki's governor

239
00:13:58,100 --> 00:14:00,180
that a riot was about
to occur in Shimabara.

240
00:14:00,180 --> 00:14:02,110
That's how he got
the army there.

241
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:05,040
So, Kaiou is using
the army to do his bidding.

242
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,280
I'd bet in his book,
he'll say that Shogo

243
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,200
will be killed
by the government.

244
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,260
He'll use the anger
Shogo's followers feel

245
00:14:10,260 --> 00:14:12,200
towards the authorities
to steamroll his way

246
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,160
into becoming
the ruler of Japan!

247
00:14:14,160 --> 00:14:16,200
With 10,000 followers
behind him, he'll take

248
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,090
over in no time.

249
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:21,150
How are we gonna stand a chance
of stopping this megalomaniac?

250
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:23,080
Well, whatever it takes
to stop this fiend,

251
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:25,170
we have to do it or
Japan will be destroyed!

252
00:14:25,170 --> 00:14:27,280
(coughing)

253
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:30,220
I really wish I could stop him.

254
00:14:30,220 --> 00:14:33,010
Shogo went to Holy Hill.

255
00:14:33,010 --> 00:14:35,040
All the villagers
went with him.

256
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:35,395
If the army--

257
00:14:35,395 --> 00:14:39,040
(coughing)

258
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,130
That sounds like tuberculosis.

259
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:43,110
No, it can't be that!

260
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:45,190
I still think it would
be wise to have Dr. Elsten

261
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:47,130
examine her just in case.

262
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:48,090
That's right!

263
00:14:48,090 --> 00:14:49,270
That Dutch guy's a doctor!

264
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:51,130
I'd forgotten all about that.

265
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:53,280
Sano, leave right now!

266
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:54,280
You really mean it?

267
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:58,120
♪

268
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,240
And when you see Dr. Elsten,
don't forget to tell him

269
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:04,070
about the situation
regarding Shogo and the army!

270
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:07,010
Maybe Dr. Elsten can stop
the army from attacking Shogo

271
00:15:07,010 --> 00:15:10,210
and his people, and explain
to him Kaiou's plans!

272
00:15:10,210 --> 00:15:12,110
I guess we'd
better get moving.

273
00:15:12,110 --> 00:15:13,170
You mean to Holy Hill?

274
00:15:13,170 --> 00:15:14,280
We can't allow all those poor,

275
00:15:14,280 --> 00:15:17,110
innocent villagers
to be massacred.

276
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:19,100
You're right about that.

277
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:21,010
We've got to talk Shogo Amakusa

278
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:22,060
out of this thing.

279
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:57,130
♪

280
00:15:57,130 --> 00:15:58,280
Sir!

281
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,200
Steady, Trigger!

282
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:06,120
The 12th Infantry is in
position and ready, sir!

283
00:16:14,070 --> 00:16:16,220
It is certainly
going to be a hot day.

284
00:16:19,040 --> 00:17:08,030
♪

285
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:10,050
It certainly is a hot day.

286
00:17:10,050 --> 00:17:13,030
It appears that the trip
across the water from Shimabara

287
00:17:13,030 --> 00:17:15,130
has made your poor little
sister sick, Shogo.

288
00:17:15,130 --> 00:17:18,160
Uncle Hyouei, I want
to ask you something.

289
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:22,180
I want you to teach me
Hiten Mitsurugi style, please?

290
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:24,210
I want to learn
to be the greatest,

291
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:25,210
the best.

292
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:26,260
I want to be a god

293
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:29,030
when it comes
to swordsmanship.

294
00:17:29,030 --> 00:17:31,130
Just like God,
I want to save people

295
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:33,290
and I want to protect
my sister, Sayo.

296
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:35,260
We lost so many
good Christian friends

297
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:38,200
on the Holy Hill on Shimabara.

298
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,210
Most of all, I want
to punish those people

299
00:17:40,210 --> 00:17:44,280
who killed my parents
in cold blood.

300
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:48,140
I am so proud to hear
you say that, Shogo.

301
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:50,010
I have always felt
that it was truly

302
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,200
my destiny to teach you.

303
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:54,290
I feel like you have been
chosen specifically by God.

304
00:17:54,290 --> 00:17:58,190
I will teach you
the Hiten Mitsurugi sword style.

305
00:17:58,190 --> 00:18:00,170
You can't use
that style to kill.

306
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:02,060
Why?

307
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:03,220
Hiten Mitsurugi
is a style used

308
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:05,250
to defend people,
it's not used to attack

309
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:08,030
or kill unless you
have no other choice.

310
00:18:08,030 --> 00:18:10,280
You must lose your hatred,
otherwise you will never

311
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:13,030
attain true Hiten
Mitsurugi greatness.

312
00:18:13,030 --> 00:18:15,140
Becoming God is impossible,
but at least you'll be able

313
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:16,290
to protect Sayo.

314
00:18:16,290 --> 00:18:18,110
You must understand
this sword style

315
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:19,190
is to help people.

316
00:18:19,190 --> 00:18:21,060
It was not created
to quench your thirst

317
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:22,230
for revenge.

318
00:18:22,230 --> 00:18:25,080
(thunder)

319
00:18:29,030 --> 00:18:30,140
No matter what you say, Uncle,

320
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:32,130
it is my destiny.

321
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:34,020
I know I will become a god.

322
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:37,040
(thunder)

323
00:18:41,020 --> 00:18:43,120
"Becoming God
is impossible, Shogo,

324
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:46,090
but at least you'll
be able to protect Sayo...

325
00:18:46,090 --> 00:18:48,270
be able to protect Sayo...

326
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:51,200
protect Sayo."

327
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:55,030
I saw mother and
father in my dream.

328
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:58,000
I'll be joining
them very soon now.

329
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:02,020
I can't wait--
we'll be together again.

330
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:03,060
Sayo.

331
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:09,270
♪

332
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:12,100
It's time for you to say
goodbye to Shimabara,

333
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,150
Sir Kaiou.

334
00:19:13,150 --> 00:19:15,080
(chuckles)

335
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:17,130
When you return, you'll
be our country's leader

336
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:20,010
with hundreds of thousands
of faithful followers,

337
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:22,120
all thanks to
your brilliant plan.

338
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:24,240
Soon, the army
surrounding Holy Hill

339
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:27,090
will attack
and Shogo Amakusa

340
00:19:27,090 --> 00:19:31,160
and 88 of his followers
will be shot to death!

341
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:33,190
Yes, 88 of them!

342
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:36,080
It's a good number
and, more importantly,

343
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:38,070
it matches the number
that I have featured

344
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:42,030
in my book that prophesizes
Shogo's untimely death.

345
00:19:42,030 --> 00:19:45,040
I'm only sorry I can't see
that child of God squeal

346
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:47,130
like a pig as he dies!

347
00:19:47,130 --> 00:19:49,000
(chuckles)

348
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,100
We'd better go, Sir Kaiou.

349
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:51,140
The steamship is waiting

350
00:19:51,140 --> 00:19:52,220
for us offshore.

351
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:53,160
Quite.

352
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,040
Kaiou!

353
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,170
Hey, it's Shozo!

354
00:19:55,170 --> 00:19:57,070
You're lucky I've been
taught to be a Christian

355
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,220
or I'd tear you apart
with my bare hands!

356
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:01,200
You're making me regret
that I have sworn never

357
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,240
to kill another human being!

358
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:06,280
God grant me the
strength to not kill you!

359
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:09,080
I just love a good animal story,

360
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:12,040
even if it is
from Amakusa's dog!

361
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,060
That's it!

362
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,080
Die!

363
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:30,050
♪

364
00:20:30,050 --> 00:20:32,090
I've heard, "Let
sleeping dogs lie,"

365
00:20:32,090 --> 00:20:35,160
but this runt had to die!

366
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:37,240
Well, it was my pleasure
to give you a first class

367
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:39,160
ticket to the Resurrection.

368
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:43,010
(chuckling)

369
00:20:43,010 --> 00:20:45,000
I feel like King of the World!

370
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,290
(cackling)

371
00:20:46,290 --> 00:20:58,160
♪

372
00:20:58,160 --> 00:21:01,020
Forgive me, Lady Magdalia.

373
00:21:01,020 --> 00:21:05,050
I beg of you, forgive
me for what I do.

374
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,220
Let's go.

375
00:21:09,220 --> 00:21:10,290
Huh?

376
00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:15,000
Huh?

377
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,100
♪

378
00:21:17,100 --> 00:21:18,190
(explosion)

379
00:21:18,190 --> 00:21:54,190
♪

380
00:21:54,190 --> 00:21:57,100
Sir Shogo, we just
heard an explosion!

381
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:59,040
The army has us surrounded!

382
00:21:59,040 --> 00:21:59,422
(gasps)

383
00:21:59,422 --> 00:22:08,180
♪

384
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:10,210
Captain, all our troops await
your order to attack, sir.

385
00:22:10,210 --> 00:22:13,180
♪

386
00:22:13,180 --> 00:22:14,230
Mm-hmm.

387
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:17,180
♪

388
00:22:17,180 --> 00:22:21,150
From what I can make out,
Holy Hill is already surrounded.

389
00:22:21,150 --> 00:22:24,070
Does that mean
the attack's gonna start?

390
00:22:24,070 --> 00:22:26,050
Kenshin, what should we do?

391
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:27,110
We must somehow stop them.

392
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:32,180
♪

393
00:22:32,180 --> 00:22:35,010
Sayo, as much as
I care about you,

394
00:22:35,010 --> 00:22:37,010
I will not let you die.

395
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:39,000
You must live.

396
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:42,270
I made a solemn vow to Shozo
and to myself to protect you,

397
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:45,060
no matter what the cost.

398
00:22:45,060 --> 00:22:47,150
♪

399
00:22:49,050 --> 00:25:12,290
♪

